Symposium "Bone Academy"
       Hôtel La Barcarolle 1197 - Prangins
     * Séminaire 26.09.2019 14:00 – 15:00

Turbulent black holes
       I will demonstrate that forced black hole horizons exhibit
       statistically steady turbulent dynamics consistent with
       Kolmogorov’s theory of 1941. I will focus on the simplest context
       for studying black hole dynamics: asymptotically anti-de Sitter
       spacetimes…
       Ecole de Physique / Room 234
     * Séminaire 26.09.2019 14:15

On the skein module of the product of a surface and a circle (Gregor Masbaum,
IMJ-PRG, CNRS)
       We show how to use Witten-Reshetikhin-Turaev invariants and
       Topological Quantum Field Theory to study skein modules of
       3-manifolds. As an application, we obtain a lower bound for the
       dimension, over the fraction field, of the Kauffman bracket skein
       module…
       Room 623, Séminaire "Topologie et Géométrie"
     * Cours public 26.09.2019 16:00 – 18:00

